{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RhPwZvpy2i5wW62icbriZj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. The current state:\n- 3-node RabbitMQ cluster running version 3.12.14 on Erlang 25.3.2.15\n- /app vhost exists with app-queue having 66 messages (durable)\n- Data is stored on emptyDir (no PVCs!) - this is important!\n\nWait, I noticed the StatefulSet uses `emptyDir` for the data volume, not a PVC. This means if we just update the image and roll the pods, the data will be lost!\nLooking at the volume configuration, the data directory is definitely backed by emptyDir, which is ephemeral. However, RabbitMQ running as a cluster should replicate queue data across nodes if they're configured as quorum queues or mirrored queues. I need to check whether app-queue is actually replicated to the other nodes in the cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1302,"cache_read_input_tokens":31699,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1302},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"e0cd9f87-6334-41f3-bad5-b1581ea6e98e","request_id":"req_011Ccdcxiv6uRs1MuDS72V4N"}
