{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016pyBZ6MJMuKgAgF2WjHMUb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The app-queue is:\n- Classic queue\n- Durable\n- Has HA policy `ha-all` which mirrors to all nodes with `ha-sync-mode: automatic`\n\nThis means the queue data is mirrored across all 3 nodes. Even though data is on emptyDir, as long as we don't restart ALL nodes simultaneously, the data will be preserved through the cluster mirroring.\n\nThe upgrade strategy should be:\n1. Rolling upgrade - restart one node at a time\n2. Before restarting each node, make sure the others have the data\n3. The HA policy ensures that when a node restarts, it will sync the queue data from the other nodes\n4. For the 3.12 to 4.1 upgrade, I need to account for the major version jump - RabbitMQ 4.0+ requires Erlang 26, and there are configuration changes like `queue_master_locator` being replaced with `queue_leader_locator` in the newer versions\n\n. The `rabbitmq:4.1-management` image should be available and suitable for this upgrade.\n\n5. The rolling upgrade strategy would involve updating the ConfigMap to fix deprecated settings, then updating the StatefulSet image. Since the pods use OrderedReady management and no persistent volumes, each pod will be recreated sequentially, and with HA mirroring in place, the data persists across the cluster during the transition.\n\nThere's a potential issue I'm starting to consider here...\n\nActually, jumping from 3.12 to 4.x is a major version change, and RabbitMQ may require all nodes to be on compatible versions during the upgrade. According to the documentation, I should enable all feature flags in 3.12 first before attempting the rolling upgrade to 4.1. The safer approach would be to enable those feature flags, update the ConfigMap for any 4.1 configuration changes, then proceed with the StatefulSet image update.\n\nI'm also noticing that `queue_master_locator` is deprecated in 4.x and needs to be replaced with `queue_leader_locator`, where the value `min-masters` becomes `balanced`. Since we're using HA mirroring with automatic sync mode, the queue data should be preserved during the rolling restart—each pod will rejoin the cluster and sync its data from the remaining mirrors automatically. and rabbitmq-1, so the automatic sync will repopulate rabbitmq-2 once it rejoins the cluster. The same process repeats for the remaining pods during the rolling update.\n\nNow I need to figure out the upgrade path itself—I should verify what RabbitMQ images are actually available and then plan the configuration changes needed for 4.1, particularly around the queue leader locator settings that changed from the older master-based approach.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":727,"cache_read_input_tokens":33001,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":727},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"43e0c231-6aec-48ab-8f4a-6dba654b1b9f","request_id":"req_011Ccdcykvg4hKy1rR6wK11Z"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_016pyBZ6MJMuKgAgF2WjHMUb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016SsBi7ubUWg7Sfq92BKGLj","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"NS=\"karma-rabbitmq-failover-first-01-2026-cf1c63a4-cluster-a\"\n# Check feature flags before upgrade\nkubectl -n $NS exec rabbitmq-0 -- rabbitmqctl list_feature_flags 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# Check what data directory structure looks like\nkubectl -n $NS exec rabbitmq-0 -- ls /var/lib/rabbitmq/ 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# Check if 4.1 image is available on nodes\ndocker images | grep rabbitmq 2>/dev/null || true\ncrictl images 2>/dev/null | grep rabbitmq || true","description":"Check feature flags, data directory, and available RabbitMQ images"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":727,"cache_read_input_tokens":33001,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":727},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"3af9d906-fbd9-4a98-8df9-f5c8ad1f277f","request_id":"req_011Ccdcykvg4hKy1rR6wK11Z"}
