{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FMYDjxjsNErgHAN4Jw3gK1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `rabbitmq:4.1-management` image is already available on the node. All feature flags are enabled in 3.12.14, which is good for the upgrade path.\n\nNow let me think about the configmap changes needed for RabbitMQ 4.1:\n\nIn RabbitMQ 4.x:\n1. `queue_master_locator` is deprecated/replaced by `queue_leader_locator`\n   - `min-masters` -> `balanced` (or just remove it)\n2. Classic mirrored queues (`ha-mode`) were deprecated in 3.x and are still supported in 4.x but deprecated\n3. Settings like `loopback_users.guest = false` and `cluster_formation.k8s.hostname_suffix` should continue working fine in 4.1\n\nThe `queue_master_locator = min-masters` deprecation won't cause a startup failure, just warnings, but I should update it to `queue_leader_locator = balanced` to align with 4.1 conventions. For the upgrade from 3.12 to 4.1, since all feature flags are already enabled and we're doing a rolling upgrade, the transition should be smooth. The queue data lives on emptyDir storage, so it's lost when a pod restarts, but since we're using HA mirroring across all three nodes, the data persists on the other replicas. As long as we do rolling restarts one node at a time and let `ha-sync-mode=automatic` resync the queues before moving to the next node, we should preserve the data through the upgrade.\n\nWhen a node restarts with an empty mnesia directory but the same Erlang cookie and node name, it should rejoin the cluster as the same node rather than becoming a new one. With Kubernetes peer discovery configured, it'll discover the other nodes and rejoin automatically.\n\nFor the upgrade strategy, I'll do a rolling update of the StatefulSet image to rabbitmq:4.1-management. The pods will restart in reverse order (rabbitmq-2, then rabbitmq-1, then rabbitmq-0), each joining the cluster with synced data while maintaining cluster health with at least 2 nodes.\n\nI also need to update the RabbitMQ configuration for 4.1 compatibility—specifically replacing the deprecated `queue_master_locator = min-masters` with `queue_leader_locator = balanced`, while keeping the guest user loopback setting as-is.\n\nI'm concerned about the mixed-version cluster state during the 3.12 to 4.1 jump, but since feature flags are already enabled and RabbitMQ's documentation supports rolling upgrades across major versions in this scenario, the temporary mixed-version state should be manageable.\n\nI also need to handle the config changes for 4.x compatibility—specifically the `queue_master_locator` to `queue_leader_locator` rename and its value mappings—so the configuration works during the transition and after the upgrade completes. I need to think through the order of operations here—updating the configmap first makes sense since the StatefulSet's rolling update will pick up both changes. I'll update the configmap with the 4.1-compatible settings, then update the image, and monitor the rolling update to ensure all pods come up healthy before verifying the cluster and queue data.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2140,"cache_read_input_tokens":33728,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2140},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"2d3b1153-67a5-42e1-9b25-1b090c79782c","request_id":"req_011Ccdd2F59Z7Tavvmp9T6SN"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FMYDjxjsNErgHAN4Jw3gK1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All feature flags are enabled and `rabbitmq:4.1-management` is already cached locally. The queue data is mirrored to all 3 nodes (`ha-mode: all`, `ha-sync-mode: automatic`), so rolling pods one at a time preserves data even with emptyDir.\n\nThe upgrade plan:\n1. Update ConfigMap with 4.1-compatible settings (`queue_leader_locator` replaces deprecated `queue_master_locator`)\n2. Update StatefulSet image to `rabbitmq:4.1-management`\n3. Monitor rolling update (ordered: rabbitmq-2 → 1 → 0)\n4. Verify cluster health and queue data"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2140,"cache_read_input_tokens":33728,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2140},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"5f4854d0-c3c6-4eb3-99fb-f4d33eb6cd33","request_id":"req_011Ccdd2F59Z7Tavvmp9T6SN"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FMYDjxjsNErgHAN4Jw3gK1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0199eutiSCUp3hcrJyv9RWr4","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"NS=\"karma-rabbitmq-failover-first-01-2026-cf1c63a4-cluster-a\"\n\n# Update ConfigMap with 4.1-compatible settings\nkubectl -n $NS apply -f - <<'EOF'\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: rabbitmq-config\n  namespace: karma-rabbitmq-failover-first-01-2026-cf1c63a4-cluster-a\ndata:\n  enabled_plugins: |\n    [rabbitmq_management,rabbitmq_peer_discovery_k8s].\n  rabbitmq.conf: |\n    cluster_formation.peer_discovery_backend = rabbit_peer_discovery_k8s\n    cluster_formation.k8s.host = kubernetes.default.svc.cluster.local\n    cluster_formation.k8s.service_name = rabbitmq-headless\n    cluster_formation.k8s.address_type = hostname\n    cluster_formation.k8s.hostname_suffix = .rabbitmq-headless.karma-rabbitmq-failover-first-01-2026-cf1c63a4-cluster-a.svc.cluster.local\n    cluster_partition_handling = pause_minority\n    queue_leader_locator = balanced\n    loopback_users = none\n    listeners.tcp.default = 5672\n    management.tcp.port = 15672\nEOF","description":"Update ConfigMap with RabbitMQ 4.1-compatible settings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2140,"cache_read_input_tokens":33728,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2140},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"63d46e4d-92ed-4be8-bb2d-43d8c1d776a9","request_id":"req_011Ccdd2F59Z7Tavvmp9T6SN"}
