{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JZ48XpiAfSf3nGZcRDGz5i","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So RabbitMQ 3.13 also can't join a 3.12 cluster due to `incompatible_feature_flags`. This is unexpected!\n\nWait, actually looking at this more carefully, this makes sense. RabbitMQ 3.13 introduces new feature flags that 3.12 doesn't support. So the same incompatibility exists for 3.12 -> 3.13 direct upgrade.\n\nThis means neither 3.13 nor 4.1 can join a 3.12 cluster in a rolling fashion due to feature flags.\nLet me examine what feature flags are currently enabled in 3.12 to understand the scope of this incompatibility.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the core issue: when 3.13 nodes try to join a 3.12 cluster, the compatibility check fails because 3.13 has required feature flags that 3.12 doesn't recognize or support. The rolling upgrade process expects the existing cluster to understand the new node's mandatory flags, but since 3.12 predates these flags, it can't validate them. The real issue is when 3.13 introduces a flag marked as \"required\" that doesn't exist in 3.12—that's what breaks compatibility. RabbitMQ does support rolling upgrades between consecutive minor versions, so the constraint is that you can't skip versions when upgrading a cluster. is working as intended, then 3.12 nodes shouldn't reject 3.13 nodes just for having unknown flags. So maybe the real issue is that 3.13 requires certain flags to be enabled that 3.12 doesn't have at all, creating a fundamental incompatibility rather than just a feature flag mismatch.\n\nI should check what version rabbitmq-2 is actually running now—whether it's still on 4.1 or if it was successfully downgraded to 3.13, since that would explain a lot about what's happening.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2276,"cache_read_input_tokens":56249,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2276},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"05c2e109-3388-4173-86a4-c423f46e0ad2","request_id":"req_011CcdeR5cPk3GGRSTjz57EC"}
