{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QeDMTCaebxtfU2hoKusQCc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have:\n- 737 messages saved with their payloads (msg-1, msg-2, msg-3, app-msg-0 to app-msg-701)\n- Definitions saved (vhosts, queues, policies, users, permissions)\n\nNow I can proceed with the upgrade. The plan:\n\n1. Update StatefulSet to 4.1-management image\n2. Scale to 0 replicas (all nodes go down together)\n3. Delete the stuck rabbitmq-2 pod (it's still running 4.1 from before)\n4. Scale to 3 replicas (all start fresh with 4.1, form a new cluster)\n5. Import definitions\n6. Re-publish messages\n7. Scale app-client back to 1\n\nBut wait—I need to think through what happens when I scale to 0. The StatefulSet will terminate rabbitmq-0 and rabbitmq-1, which are running 3.12, but rabbitmq-2 is already stuck on 4.1. I need to be careful about how the deletion and recreation works here.\n\nWhen I scale to 0, all three pods get deleted. Then scaling back to 3 with the 4.1 image means all three start fresh with empty mnesia directories, so they'll form a completely new cluster via peer discovery. After that I can import the definitions and republish the messages.\n\nActually, there's another detail I should verify—the StatefulSet's current desired image is 3.13-management from our last patch, but the running pods are mixed: rabbitmq-0 and rabbitmq-1 are still on 3.12-management, while rabbitmq-2 is already on 4.1-management from the first patch attempt.\n\nIf I scale to 0 and back to 3 with 3.13 as the target, all three pods would start with 3.13-management. But wait—3.13 might have the same feature flag incompatibility issue as 4.1. Actually no, that's not right. When all three nodes start simultaneously with 3.13 and empty mnesia directories, they're all on the same version, so there's no incompatibility. The incompatibility only happens when joining an existing cluster of a different version. Three fresh 3.13 nodes doing peer discovery will form a new cluster together without any issues. But then I'd end up on 3.13 instead of 4.1, which isn't what I want.\n\nThe real solution is to scale to 0 and then back to 3 with the 4.1-management image directly. When all three nodes start fresh simultaneously on 4.1, they form a new cluster together on the same version—no incompatibility check needed since there's no existing cluster to join. So the plan is to update the StatefulSet image to 4.1-management, scale to 0, scale back to 3, then import definitions and republish messages. Let me verify what the StatefulSet's current desired image actually is.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":359,"cache_read_input_tokens":79591,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":359},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"2747779c-3645-41a0-82ae-ae435d380fd8","request_id":"req_011CcdenF9TZTtc7QkXSC38J"}
