{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01UrW4aXncdHwQL4u8Y65RCT","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"There's a validation error on the policy import. In RabbitMQ 4.1, the `ha-mode` and `ha-sync-mode` policy settings for classic mirrored queues may no longer be valid. Classic mirrored queues (HA queues) were deprecated in RabbitMQ 3.x and removed in 4.0.\n\nFrom RabbitMQ 4.0 release notes:\n> \"Classic Mirrored Queues have been removed in RabbitMQ 4.0. They were deprecated and had no support since 3.13.\"\n \nSo the HA policy with `ha-mode: all` won't work in 4.1 anymore. I need to switch to Quorum Queues instead, which is the modern replacement for classic mirrored queues. This means I should either create the queues as quorum queues or at least remove the HA policy and create them as standard durable classic queues with 4.1-compatible policies for data protection.\n\nThe vhosts are already set up correctly, but the queues are empty and need to be created. My plan is to create the queues manually using the appropriate queue type for 4.1, set up the right policies for replication, and then republish the 737 messages that need to be preserved.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":587,"cache_read_input_tokens":88041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":587},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"55a5e8f0-c61a-44cb-a294-eac7f4089dc6","request_id":"req_011Ccdf2CHxBmtPTfkp79J2U"}
