{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HfuSaUnEZAR5pCwN5Yc8iW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Port-forward got dropped. The kubectl port-forward process was killed or timed out. Let me restart it and try again.\n\nActually, the issue is that the port-forward process (PF_PID=$!) was killed because the first Bash tool call exits and the background process is terminated with it.\n\nI need to run the port-forward in the background within the same shell session. But each Bash tool call is a fresh shell, so the PF_PID from the first call is gone.\n\nLet me restart the port-forward in the same shell as the message publication. I'll start port-forward in the background and then run the Python script in the same shell.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1138,"cache_read_input_tokens":90240,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1138},"output_tokens":15,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"d18bf8d8-6baa-4ba9-a5d4-0c7021b7f888","request_id":"req_011Ccdf5Tv8hnRDkKNFUYQug"}
