{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XRQxWUuhVvo1Hxo7dbC6Xk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Port-forward is very unstable. The connection keeps dropping after a few requests. \n\nLet me try a different approach:\n1. Copy the messages JSON file into the curl-test pod which has curl\n2. Write a shell script in the curl-test pod to publish each message using curl\n3. Run it there\n\nOr, I can use the ops-client pod which is also running and might have Python.\n\nOr I can upload the Python publish script to the curl-test pod and run it there.\n\nActually, the simplest approach:\n1. Copy messages.json to the curl-test pod\n2. Install or use an existing HTTP client in the pod to publish messages\nThe curl-test pod has curl available, so I could write a shell script to parse the messages and publish them one by one. But the JSON structure is complex, and I'd need jq to parse it properly—I should check if that's installed in the pod. Alternatively, kubectl port-forward's instability with many requests is a known issue, so running the script directly inside the cluster via kubectl exec might be more reliable, though the rabbitmq pod itself doesn't have Python available.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1356,"cache_read_input_tokens":91378,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1356},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"0df1755b-1749-421d-be99-8eb8dc008d08","request_id":"req_011Ccdf711goC1tZC7G4A8CQ"}
