{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XPpkaRMxxXeAkdyfJjixb2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The app-client is showing Error/Error state. Let me check what's happening with it. The app-client might be failing because it's trying to connect to a queue that now has a different type (quorum vs classic).\n\nLet me check the app-client logs.\n\nAlso, the message count is 1492 which matches 737 (original) + more messages. The app-client might be producing to the queue when it runs before crashing.\n\nActually wait - the message count should go up if app-client is successfully publishing. But it's in Error state. Let me check.\nThe message count stayed at 1492, so the app-client is now crashing instead of publishing. It could be failing because the queue type changed to quorum, or maybe it's having issues with the AMQP consumers trying to work with the new queue type. Though quorum queues should be backward compatible with AMQP 0.9.1, so the app-client should theoretically be able to publish and consume from it.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1115,"cache_read_input_tokens":99661,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1115},"output_tokens":16,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"e6038661-2e51-4325-b279-c2ae46a405aa","request_id":"req_011CcdfanX8nJ9Hr6XSYFB8G"}
