{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NqZJWP1nGX7cPLoKowrFHs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The app-client is trying to declare the app-queue as a \"classic\" queue, but we created it as a \"quorum\" queue. There's a conflict.\n\nThe fix:\n- The app-client is checking for the existence of the queue with `x-queue-type: classic` arguments\n- The queue now exists as `quorum` type\n- This causes a 406 PRECONDITION_FAILED error\n\nThe issue is that the app-client declares the queue with `x-queue-type: classic` on startup, which conflicts with our quorum queue.\n\nI have a few options:\n1. Delete the quorum queue and recreate it as classic (but then we lose the benefits of quorum queues)\n2. Fix the app-client to use quorum queues (but this might require modifying the app-client, which is outside the scope)\n3. Check if the original queue was classic and use classic type instead\n\nLooking back at the original setup, the queue was classic with HA mirroring policy, but RabbitMQ 4.1 removed classic mirrored queues. Classic queues themselves still exist in 4.1, so I could recreate it as a classic queue without the HA policy.\n\nThe app-client is expecting a classic queue, but we created a quorum queue instead. The solution is to delete the quorum queue and recreate it as a classic queue, though I need to verify that classic queues without mirroring are still valid in 4.1.\n\nLooking at the message timeline, we published 737 messages initially, then restored the app-client which started producing additional messages. Before the app-client began erroring, it had added about 755 new messages to the queue, bringing the total to 1492.\n\nThe real issue is that the app-client can publish messages to the existing quorum queue just fine, but it fails when trying to declare the queue with `x-queue-type: classic` because the queue already exists as a quorum queue. The error about the inequivalent `x-queue-type` argument confirms this — the app-client is attempting to redeclare a queue that's already been created with different parameters.\n\nSo I need to delete the quorum queue and recreate it as classic, which is what the app-client actually expects. original queue was classic type, so I need to convert the quorum queue back to classic. The safest approach is to export all 1492 messages from the quorum queue, delete it, recreate it as classic, and republish the messages to preserve the data while fixing the app-client compatibility issue.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":534,"cache_read_input_tokens":100776,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":534},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"6d74405a-9424-4f88-90c5-1a9735a9dd28","request_id":"req_011CcdfbZTM4TJ9VkEYr4UwA"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NqZJWP1nGX7cPLoKowrFHs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The app-client declares the queue as `classic` but finds a `quorum` queue — conflict. Since the original queue was classic type, I need to recreate app-queue as classic. Classic queues (without HA policy) still work in 4.1."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":534,"cache_read_input_tokens":100776,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":534},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"9f7ad407-1c90-413d-9e3c-952644c637bf","request_id":"req_011CcdfbZTM4TJ9VkEYr4UwA"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NqZJWP1nGX7cPLoKowrFHs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MYSL8te7eJmvwAVEeVUe9x","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"NS=\"karma-rabbitmq-failover-first-01-2026-cf1c63a4-cluster-a\"\n\n# Start port-forward, export current messages, delete quorum queue, recreate as classic, republish\nkubectl -n $NS port-forward service/rabbitmq 15672:15672 &\nPF_PID=$!\nsleep 3\n\n# Export current messages from quorum queue (which now has 1492)\npython3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport json\nimport urllib.request\nimport base64\n\nuser = 'admin'\npassword = 'adminpass'\ncreds = base64.b64encode(f'{user}:{password}'.encode()).decode()\n\nurl = 'http://localhost:15672/api/queues/%2Fapp/app-queue/get'\ndata = json.dumps({'count': 50000, 'ackmode': 'ack_requeue_true', 'encoding': 'auto'}).encode()\nreq = urllib.request.Request(url, data=data, method='POST')\nreq.add_header('Authorization', f'Basic {creds}')\nreq.add_header('Content-Type', 'application/json')\nwith urllib.request.urlopen(req) as r:\n    msgs = json.loads(r.read())\nwith open('/tmp/rmq-messages-v2.json', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(msgs, f)\nprint(f'Exported {len(msgs)} messages')\nnon_empty = [m for m in msgs if m.get('payload')]\nprint(f'Non-empty payloads: {len(non_empty)}')\nif non_empty:\n    print(f'Sample: {non_empty[:3]}')\nPYEOF\n\nkill $PF_PID 2>/dev/null || true","description":"Export current 1492 messages from quorum queue","timeout":120000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":534,"cache_read_input_tokens":100776,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":534},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9428bb29-e5b2-4a20-b8cb-0b98077d2c13","uuid":"48f8d7c